reviewText: I have been a pretty big advocate of ANTI Suicide girls ever since they A) rejected me in 2003 and B) got lousy press coverage after the model scandal but I still try and keep an open mind. After just watching this I would like my time back. The majority of girls are not that attractive and if that is not bad enough for a 'skin' T & A flick, they don't really have much personality going for them either. And they definitely can't act!  They come off as spoiled, attention whores who are washed up and trashy. At least the First Tour DVD and Italian Villa DVD had cuter girls with personalities, charm and charisma. I think in general the site has REALLY gone down hill in terms of character and caliber since the scandal but this was a pretty weak attempt at trying to cater to horny men(women) and horror fans. The film has no blood, gore or suspense. I wouldn't waste your time on this as site co-owner Missy Suicide is well on her way to being successful at killing off her Suicide Girl company.
